//Remove Magic
@63002 = ~Wand of Remove Magic~
@63003 = ~Intended for use during combat, this wand dispels the magical effects upon any enemies within the area. This includes effects given from spells, potions, and certain magical items such as wands. It does not, however, affect enchanted magical items. The chance of the dispel succeeding is determined by this wand's caster level (%caster_level%) and the level of the magic being dispelled. The base chance of successfully dispelling is 50%. For every level that this wand's caster level (%caster_level%) exceeds the original protection's caster level, the chance of success increases by 5%; conversely, for every level that it falls below, the chance of success decreases by 10%. However, despite the difference in levels, there is always at least a 1% chance of success or failure. Intuitively, this spell is almost useless if the target is 5 or more levels higher than the caster.

Thus, a difference of +10 levels higher than the magic it is trying to dispel, there is only a 1% chance of failure. Similarly, if the caster level is 4 levels lower than the magic the wielder is trying to dispel, there is only a 10% chance of success.

Note: While this spell dispels the individual effects of Grease, Web, Stinking Cloud and other such spells, it does not dispel the area of effect.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Remove Magic
