@63048 = ~Wand of Dispel Magic~
@63049 = ~With targeting this wand, it removes magical effects upon anyone within the area. This includes effects given from spells, potions and certain magical items such as wands. It does not, however, affect enchanted magical items or spell protections such as Spell Turning and Spell Deflection.

The chance of the dispel succeeding is determined by the level of this wand (%caster_level%) and the level of the magic being dispelled. The base chance of successfully dispelling is 50%. For every level that Dispel Magic's caster level (%caster_level%) is above the original caster, its chance of success increases by 5%. For every caster level that Dispel Magic is below the original caster, its chance of success decreases by 10%. However, despite the difference in levels, there is always at least a 5% chance of success or failure. Thus, if Dispel Magic is 10 caster levels higher than the magic it is trying to dispel, there is only a 5% chance of failure. Similarly if Dispel Magic is 4 levels lower than the magic it is trying to dispel, there is only a 10% chance of success. Intuitively, this spell is almost useless if the target is 5 or more levels higher than the caster.

Note: While this spell dispels the individual effects of Grease, Web, Stinking Cloud, and other such spells, it does not dispel the area of effect.

