 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Improved Invisibility
@64008 = ~Wand of Improved Invisibility~
@64009 = ~This wand causes a creature touched to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or its gear, unless these allies can normally see invisible things or employ magic to do so. Items dropped or put down by the invisible creature become visible, items picked up disappear if tucked into the clothing or pouches worn by the creature. Of course, the invisible creature is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render the creature detectable.

The invisibility remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled. Subtle hints —a shimmering— allow an observant opponent to attack the invisible spell recipient; these traces are only noticeable when specifically looked for (after the invisible character has made <PRO_HISHER> presence known†). The caster can, however, cast defensive spells on <PRO_HIMHER>self and fellow party members.

Note: After taking revealing action, the wielder is no longer completely invisible. Opponents can target the target (but not target them with spells).

†: missile discharge, melee combat, opening doors, disarming a trap, opening a chest, or spellcasting.

STATISTICS:
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Charge abilities:
– Improved Invisibility
  – Applies a lasting invisibility to target
    – +4 bonus to Armor Class
    – +4 bonus to Saving throws
  Range: Touch
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Minor Globe of Invulnerability
@64010 = ~Wand of Minor Globe of Invulnerability~
@64011 = ~Once activated, this wand creates a faintly shimmering magical sphere around the caster that prevents any 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell effects from penetrating (i.e., the area of effect of any such spells does not include the area of the Minor Globe of Invulnerability). This includes innate abilities and effects from devices. However, any type of spell can be cast out of the magical sphere, and these pass from the caster of the globe to their subject without affecting the globe. Spells of 4th level or higher are not affected by the globe.

STATISTICS:
(Abjuration)

Charge abilities:
– Minor Globe of Invulnerability
  – Globe that prevents any spell effects from penetrating
    – 1st level
    – 2nd level
    – 3rd level
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Monster Summoning II
@64012 = ~Wand of Monster Summoning II~
@64013 = ~This wand summons a random selection of 4-HD monsters. There is a 60% chance of receiving one monster and a 40% chance of receiving two monsters. The monster(s) appear within spell range and attack the wielder's opponents until the spell duration expires or until they are slain.

STATISTICS:
(Conjuration/Summoning)

Charge abilities:
– Monster Summoning II
  – Summons 1 or 2 monsters of 4 HD
  Range: 120 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Summons
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Stoneskin
@64018 = ~Wand of Stoneskin~
@64019 = ~Upon activating this wand, an outer skin of stone will move up from the ground, completely covering the wielder. This skin is of course magical and will hinder the wielder in no way. The effect of this is to protect <PRO_HIMHER> from physical attacks such as melee weapons and projectiles. For each of the %magnitude% skins the wielder possesses, the spell will stop one attack. The skins will remain on the wielder until <PRO_HESHE> is affected by a Dispel Magic, all of the skins are removed due to physical attacks, or the spell duration expires.

It is important to note that this will not protect the wielder from any magical attacks, such as Fireball.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Stoneskin
  – Conjures %magnitude% layers of protective skins
  Duration: 12 hours
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Contagion
@64020 = ~Wand of Contagion~
@64021 = ~Once activated, this wand causes a major disease and weakness in a creature. The afflicted individual is immediately stricken with painful and distracting symptoms: boils, blotches, lesions, seeping abscesses, and so on. Strength, Dexterity, and Charisma scores are reduced by 2. The afflicted character is also Slowed. These effects persist until the character receives a Cure Disease spell.

STATISTICS:
(Necromancy)

Charge abilities:
– Contagion
  – -2 penalty to Strength
  – -2 penalty to Dexterity
  – -2 penalty to Charisma
  – Slowed
  Range: 90 ft.
  Duration: Permanent
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Emotion, Hopelessness
@64022 = ~Wand of Emotion, Hopelessness~
@64023 = ~Upon activation, this wand can disturb the emotional state of those around the target location. The effect of this is to inflict a feeling of hopelessness upon the enemies within the visual range of the wielder. Upon a failed Saving Throw vs. Wand, the affected creature will lie down where they stand and give over all their will to a higher power. Sometimes they can be heard to exclaim things such as "I lay down and die," or "I'm going home." This will last for the duration of the spell, upon which they will return to normal.

The secondary effect of this spell is to instill upon the wielder the feeling of courage. This will remove any effects of panic and restore <PRO_HISHER> morale, as well as prevent the above from creeping forth into <PRO_HISHER> psyche. There is no Saving Throw vs. this and it will last for the duration of the spell. It will, however, be affected by Magic Resistance and other such things.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Emotion, Hopelessness
  – Enemies:
    Lay down in defeat
  – Wielder:
    Protection from Fear
  Range: 50 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates prone effect

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Greater Malison
@64024 = ~Wand of Greater Malison~
@64025 = ~Activating this wand, the wielder may adversely affect all the Saving Throws of <PRO_HISHER> enemies. The effect is applied to all hostile creatures within the area of effect. Opponents under the influence of this spell make all Saving Throws at a penalty of -4.

STATISTICS:
(Enchantment/Charm)

Charge abilities:
– Greater Malison
  – -4 penalty to all saving throws
  Range: 50 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Otiluke's Resilient Sphere
@64026 = ~Wand of Otiluke's Resilient Sphere~
@64027 = ~After selecting a target and activating this wand, it conjures a globe of shimmering force that encloses the subject creature if it fails to Save vs. Wand. The resilient sphere will contain its subject for the duration of the spell. The sphere is completely immune to all damage; in fact, the only method of removing the sphere is a successful Dispel Magic. Hence, the creature caught inside the globe is completely safe from all attacks, but at the same time completely unable to affect the outside world.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Otiluke's Resilient Sphere
  – Excludes target from combat
  Range: 40 ft.
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Spirit Armor
@64028 = ~Wand of Spirit Armor~
@64029 = ~Upon activating this wand, it taps in to the target's life force in order to create an incorporeal barrier around the target's body for the duration of the spell. The armor itself is weightless and does not hinder movement or spellcasting at all.

The spirit armor does not work cumulatively with any other armor; however, Dexterity bonuses still apply as well as magic rings and shields. While in effect, the Armor Class of the recipient will be set to 1, as if <PRO_HESHE> were wearing full plate. Also, due to the magical nature of the spell, <PRO_HESHE> will also receive a +3 bonus to Save vs. Spell.

When the spell runs out, the external portion of the spirit is temporarily lost, inflicting 2d4 points of damage upon the target unless the creature makes a Saving Throw vs. Spell.

STATISTICS:
(Necromancy)

Charge abilities:
– Spirit Armor
  – Base armor class of 1
  – +3 bonus to Save vs. Spell
  Damage: 2d4 magic damage when spell expires
  Range: Touch
  Duration: 2 hours
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Wand negates damage

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Polymorph Other
@64030 = ~Wand of Polymorph Other~
@64031 = ~Once activated, this wand permanently alters the form of the creature affected. Mental attributes are not affected, and the target does not receive the special abilities of the new form. However all physical attributes are changed to adhere to the new form. This is a specific version of the spell in that the recipient will be transformed into a squirrel unless a Save vs. Petrification/Polymorph is made successfully. The transformation is instant and permanent until a Dispel Magic is cast successfully upon the affected creature. The natural attacks of the new form also become available and all clothes and equipment that the target was wearing will mold into the new form.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Polymorph Other
  – Turns target into a squirrel
  Range: Sight
  Duration: Permanent
  Area of Effect: 1 creature
  Saving Throw: Save vs. Petrification negates

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Polymorph Self
@64032 = ~Wand of Polymorph Self~
@64033 = ~Upon activating this wand, the wielder can transform into any of several new forms (at any time and as many times as <PRO_HESHE> wishes). The wielder gains the natural attacks of the new form in some cases and may use weapons in others. The mental attributes of the wielder remain the same, but all physical attributes are obtained from the new form. Also, any natural protections that the new form offers are conferred to the wielder, such as the resistance to missile and crushing weapons possessed by the slime form.

The wielder also gains the physical mode of locomotion and breathing as well. This spell does not give the new form's other abilities, such as special attacks and magic, nor does it run the risk of the wielder changing personality and mentality.

The possible forms given by Polymorph Self are:
– Flind: wields a magical halberd (+1 fire damage and strikes as a +3 weapon)
– Mustard Jelly: capable of poisoning or slowing opponents (if they fail a Save vs. Death when hit)
– Ogre: Capable of causing massive damage
– Spider: Causes poison damage when it hits an opponent

In addition, the wielder may choose the form of brown bear, black bear, or wolf.

STATISTICS:
(Alteration)

Charge abilities:
– Polymorph Self
  – Gain ability to polymorph self
  Duration: %duration%
  Area of Effect: Self
  Saving Throw: None

Requires:
 9 Intelligence

Weight: 1~


//Enchanted Weapon
@64034 = ~Wand of Enchanted Weapon~
@64035 = ~This wand enchants any weapons that the wielder currently holds. For the duration of the spell, those weapons are treated as having a +3 enchantment for the purposes of determining what they can hit.

